<Main>
  <ContentSection>
    <:header>
      Why even this addon?
    </:header>
    <:content>
      <div>
        <p class="mb-4">Forms aren't exactly a new thing, so why this addon?
          Existing solutions are either not using the latest Ember paradigms
          (Octane/Polaris), generate specific markup and thus hard to customize
          or coupled to a specific validation library. ember-headless-form is
          none of this. It gives you all the flexibility, without having to
          reinvent the wheel.</p>
        <p>It tries to solve these main problems:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
          <li>Getting data in and out of the from</li>
          <li>Rendering semantic form markup, accessible by default</li>
          <li>Provide rich support for client-side validation</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </:content>
  </ContentSection>

